The paper deals with data integration between web sources and relational data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The authors propose a system that uses input-output examples to join semi-structured web data with relational data in spreadsheets, which involves techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system is designed to be user-friendly for data scientists and end-users with diverse backgrounds, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
